(1840, 'XPeng to buy Didi\'s smart car business for $774 million', 'Chinese EV company XPeng (XPEV) announced that it will be buying Didi\'s (DIDIY) smart car unit in a deal worth up to $774 million. Yahoo Finance Reporter Pras Subramanian explains the advantages of the deal, saying that “XPeng is getting Didi’s expertise with ride-hailing and autonomous technology.” Subramanian notes the competitiveness within the Chinese EV space and that XPeng’s new deal with Didi could help it get an edge over the competition.', '2023-08-29 12:36:34', '2023-08-29 12:36:34'),
