(2719, 'Ford unveils new Tesla challenge aimed at electrifying corporate fleets', 'One of the biggest challenges to broader electric vehicle adoption is a lack of infrastructure.  One of the biggest consumer hesitations around EVs involves concerns over range and charging; a proper fast-charging infrastructure spread across the country resolves those concerns.  A series of big-name legacy automakers have inked deals with the EV leader over the past few months that would grant them access to Tesla\'s Supercharging network, namely Ford  and General Motors .', '2023-08-30 07:11:26', '2023-08-30 07:11:26'),
