(4008, 'Tesla\'s hidden \'Elon Mode\' has NHTSA regulators extremely concerned', 'Despite its name, Tesla\'s Full Self-Driving technology is not actually fully self-driving.  Both FSD and Autopilot require the constant supervision of the driver with eyes on the road and hands on the wheel; the car is designed to \"nag\" the driver if and when that supervision lags.  Nicknamed \"Elon Mode,\" this iteration of self-driving was discovered by a hacker who then drove 600 miles with it enabled.', '2023-08-30 17:10:03', '2023-08-30 17:10:03'),
